Otherwise your condition

283
00:23:00.050 --> 00:23:04.010
will deteriorate.

284
00:23:05.420 --> 00:23:08.190
Get up. Can you play with me?

285
00:23:08.390 --> 00:23:10.420
We have about 20 minutes.

286
00:23:10.930 --> 00:23:14.360
I have a new anesthetic.

287
00:23:10.930 --> 00:23:14.360
Do you want to try it out?

288
00:23:14.700 --> 00:23:15.690
Yes.

289
00:23:16.370 --> 00:23:19.390
The one who wakes up first

290
00:23:16.370 --> 00:23:19.390
will be the winner.

291
00:23:25.140 --> 00:23:27.080
Don't put more on mine.

292
00:23:34.750 --> 00:23:37.150
One. two. three.

293
00:24:17.090 --> 00:24:20.790
It's nearly finished.

294
00:24:17.090 --> 00:24:20.790
It needs floor tiles and lights.

295
00:24:21.000 --> 00:24:23.630
I can't decide which one I prefer.

296
00:24:29.770 --> 00:24:33.470
- I like these.

297
00:24:29.770 --> 00:24:33.470
- I prefer those.

298
00:24:33.980 --> 00:24:35.740
Those are nice too.

299
00:24:36.550 --> 00:24:38.540
- How's your wife?

300
00:24:36.550 --> 00:24:38.540
- Same.

301
00:24:38.980 --> 00:24:41.780
- Do you go out?

302
00:24:38.980 --> 00:24:41.780
- No.

303
00:24:42.450 --> 00:24:45.720
I told you. you should.

304
00:24:42.450 --> 00:24:45.720
Even if she's in a wheelchair.

305
00:24:45.960 --> 00:24:48.620
She's unwell.

306
00:24:45.960 --> 00:24:48.620
And she doesn't like visitors.

307
00:24:48.820 --> 00:24:52.520
I've told her hundreds of times

308
00:24:48.820 --> 00:24:52.520
to invite you for a beer.

309
00:24:52.730 --> 00:24:53.990
I understand.

310
00:24:54.200 --> 00:24:56.560
It's tragic what happened to her.

311
00:24:56.800 --> 00:24:59.170
It requires great

312
00:24:56.800 --> 00:24:59.170
psychological strength.

313
00:24:59.370 --> 00:25:02.360
In the picture. she looks energetic.

314
00:25:02.570 --> 00:25:04.300
She was a volleyball champion?

315
00:25:04.510 --> 00:25:05.570
Handball.

316
00:25:09.210 --> 00:25:10.510
These you said?

317
00:25:10.710 --> 00:25:12.810
Yes. The others are nice too.

318
00:25:49.050 --> 00:25:50.110
Hi. honey.

319
00:25:51.420 --> 00:25:54.360
I had a meeting.

320
00:25:51.420 --> 00:25:54.360
A meeting. yes.

321
00:25:55.360 --> 00:25:58.450
Did they go out? Or work out?

322
00:25:58.690 --> 00:26:02.460
Why. what's the matter?

323
00:25:58.690 --> 00:26:02.460
Her belly or her stomach?

324
00:26:03.230 --> 00:26:04.430
Yes. it's cold outside.

325
00:26:45.440 --> 00:26:47.740
I'd like my dog back.

326
00:26:52.950 --> 00:26:56.080
Sorry. I can't do that.

327
00:26:56.290 --> 00:27:00.310
He's still on the second stage

328
00:26:56.290 --> 00:27:00.310
of his training.

329
00:27:02.690 --> 00:27:04.250
I'll show you.

330
00:27:13.440 --> 00:27:15.770
First stage. second stage—

331
00:27:15.970 --> 00:27:17.500
where your dog is—

332
00:27:17.710 --> 00:27:20.540
third. fourth. fifth

333
00:27:17.710 --> 00:27:20.540
and final stage.

334
00:27:29.050 --> 00:27:30.820
Let me explain.

335
00:27:31.690 --> 00:27:33.320
Dogs are like clay

336
00:27:33.790 --> 00:27:37.950
and our job here is to mold them.

337
00:27:39.290 --> 00:27:41.160
A dog may be energetic.

338
00:27:42.200 --> 00:27:46.130
a fighter. cowardly. or gentle.

339
00:27:48.070 --> 00:27:52.910
All this requires work. patience

340
00:27:48.070 --> 00:27:52.910
and care from us.

341
00:27:53.540 --> 00:27:56.740
Every dog is waiting for us

342
00:27:56.980 --> 00:27:59.350
to show it how it should behave.

343
00:28:00.320 --> 00:28:02.380
Do you understand?

344
00:28:02.750 --> 00:28:05.310
So the issue here

345
00:28:05.520 --> 00:28:10.590
is to decide together

346
00:28:05.520 --> 00:28:10.590
how we want your dog to behave.

347
00:28:11.530 --> 00:28:16.190
Do we want an animal

348
00:28:11.530 --> 00:28:16.190
or do we want a friend?

349
00:28:19.100 --> 00:28:22.940
Do we want a guard

350
00:28:19.100 --> 00:28:22.940
who will respect us as his masters

351
00:28:23.770 --> 00:28:27.210
and do unhesitatingly

352
00:28:23.770 --> 00:28:27.210
whatever we ask of him?

353
00:28:28.210 --> 00:28:29.770
You see?

354
00:28:30.180 --> 00:28:31.270
Sure.

355
00:28:41.590 --> 00:28:42.610
Rex!

356
00:28:45.290 --> 00:28:46.350
Rex!

357
00:30:53.760 --> 00:30:55.220
1 min. 15 sec.

358
00:31:08.700 --> 00:31:09.830
2 min.

359
00:31:16.880 --> 00:31:18.350
2 min. 30 sec.

360
00:31:21.580 --> 00:31:23.450
2 min. 45 sec.

361
00:31:32.130 --> 00:31:33.890
3 min. 15 sec.

362
00:31:43.370 --> 00:31:45.200
3 min. 45 sec.

363
00:32:02.960 --> 00:32:04.980
4 min. 30 sec.

364
00:32:13.500 --> 00:32:15.560
5 min. 15 sec.

365
00:32:21.340 --> 00:32:23.140
5 min. 30 sec.

366
00:34:00.280 --> 00:34:02.370
What do you mean you can't?

367
00:34:04.110 --> 00:34:05.600
I'm sorry.

368
00:34:06.520 --> 00:34:09.950
We're doing this for you.

369
00:34:06.520 --> 00:34:09.950
not for me.

370
00:34:10.190 --> 00:34:11.520
I'm sorry.

371
00:34:12.620 --> 00:34:16.580
Try again but use your tongue.

372
00:34:12.620 --> 00:34:16.580
There's no point otherwise.

373
00:34:26.600 --> 00:34:28.260
Don't tell Dad.

374
00:34:29.200 --> 00:34:31.040
- Do you feel disgusted?

375
00:34:29.200 --> 00:34:31.040
- No.

376
00:34:31.410 --> 00:34:32.810
Then what?

377
00:34:34.810 --> 00:34:37.250
I prefer what we did last time.

378
00:34:53.230 --> 00:34:54.090
Hello.

379
00:34:57.170 --> 00:34:58.430
What are you doing?

380
00:34:58.970 --> 00:35:02.460
Cleaning the carpet

381
00:34:58.970 --> 00:35:02.460
to keep germs off it.

382
00:35:14.820 --> 00:35:18.340
- Do you want this headband?

383
00:35:14.820 --> 00:35:18.340
- Yes. very much.

384
00:35:18.990 --> 00:35:20.820
What are you going to give me?

385
00:35:26.660 --> 00:35:29.530
How about this pencil?

386
00:35:26.660 --> 00:35:29.530
It has an eraser on it.

387
00:35:29.760 --> 00:35:30.750
No.

388
00:35:37.440 --> 00:35:38.930
A tape measure?

389
00:35:40.180 --> 00:35:43.010
You press here

390
00:35:40.180 --> 00:35:43.010
and it reels in by itself.

391
00:35:43.810 --> 00:35:44.840
No.

392
00:35:56.060 --> 00:35:59.960
Come closer and lick for a while

393
00:35:56.060 --> 00:35:59.960
and the headband is yours.

394
00:36:01.630 --> 00:36:03.000
Are you disgusted?

395
00:36:03.400 --> 00:36:04.460
No.

396
00:36:30.350 --> 00:36:33.080
- Do you want to dance?

397
00:36:30.350 --> 00:36:33.080
- I don't feel like it.

398
00:36:33.320 --> 00:36:38.220
Besides. we don't have time.

399
00:36:33.320 --> 00:36:38.220
We have to go meet Mom.

400
00:36:38.430 --> 00:36:42.560
Mom will be late. She's talking

401
00:36:38.430 --> 00:36:42.560
to herself again in her room.

402
00:36:43.160 --> 00:36:45.360
Are you afraid of Mom

403
00:36:43.160 --> 00:36:45.360
talking to herself?

404
00:36:45.570 --> 00:36:46.690
Not at all.

405
00:36:46.900 --> 00:36:48.330
- You are afraid.

406
00:36:46.900 --> 00:36:48.330
- I'm not.

407
00:36:49.000 --> 00:36:50.270
- You are.

408
00:36:49.000 --> 00:36:50.270
- No.

409
00:36:50.900 --> 00:36:54.170
You can't hear her.

410
00:36:50.900 --> 00:36:54.170
She might be talking about you.

411
00:36:54.370 --> 00:36:55.770
Stop it.

412
00:37:02.680 --> 00:37:05.210
If I give you a present.

413
00:37:02.680 --> 00:37:05.210
will you lick me?

414
00:37:05.420 --> 00:37:07.750
- What kind of present?

415
00:37:05.420 --> 00:37:07.750
- A headband.

416
00:37:07.950 --> 00:37:09.390
I already have one.

417
00:37:09.620 --> 00:37:12.060
This one sparkles in the dark.

418
00:37:12.260 --> 00:37:14.120
What do you mean by sparkles?

419
00:37:14.890 --> 00:37:16.060
It lights up.

420
00:37:16.960 --> 00:37:18.400
Where did you get it?

421
00:37:18.600 --> 00:37:20.090
I can't tell you.

422
00:37:20.470 --> 00:37:23.530
Do our parents know

423
00:37:20.470 --> 00:37:23.530
you have a headband like that?

424
00:37:25.370 --> 00:37:28.400
So. it could easily be yours.

425
00:37:30.640 --> 00:37:32.370
What do you want me to lick?

426
00:37:34.080 --> 00:37:35.310
My shoulder.

427
00:37:50.500 --> 00:37:53.930
Can you get some chocolate

428
00:37:50.500 --> 00:37:53.930
if you pass by the shop?

429
00:37:54.130 --> 00:37:56.970
Don't go out of your way.

430
00:38:00.170 --> 00:38:01.510
Any kind.

431
00:38:09.950 --> 00:38:10.970
Me too.

432
00:39:17.220 --> 00:39:19.020
That isn't yours.

433
00:39:20.550 --> 00:39:21.820
Leave me alone.

434
00:40:35.030 --> 00:40:37.020
- Does it still hurt?

435
00:40:35.030 --> 00:40:37.020
- Yes.

436
00:40:40.030 --> 00:40:44.200
You could ask Dad to get in the car

437
00:40:40.030 --> 00:40:44.200
and fetch it for you.

438
00:40:44.400 --> 00:40:47.030
That's what I'd do if I were you.

439
00:40:47.240 --> 00:40:48.830
It's the only way.

440
00:40:53.480 --> 00:40:54.500
Dad!

441
00:40:58.690 --> 00:41:01.750
The eldest threw the airplane

442
00:40:58.690 --> 00:41:01.750
over the fence.

443
00:41:01.990 --> 00:41:04.420
- Where?

444
00:41:01.990 --> 00:41:04.420
- There. on the road.

445
00:41:05.590 --> 00:41:06.920
I'll try.

446
00:43:33.240 --> 00:43:35.140
How did it happen?

447
00:43:36.740 --> 00:43:38.230
What did you tell them?

448
00:43:39.850 --> 00:43:41.870
You did the right thing.

449
00:43:42.480 --> 00:43:44.210
I'll tell them as well.

450
00:43:45.150 --> 00:43:48.050
Yes. it's a good opportunity.

451
00:43:48.520 --> 00:43:49.550
<i>Yes.</i>

452
00:43:51.290 --> 00:43:54.820
<i>The temperature will rise</i>

453
00:43:51.290 --> 00:43:54.820
<i>and the wind will drop.</i>

454
00:43:57.460 --> 00:43:59.630
<i>Five or six degrees.</i>

455
00:44:01.030 --> 00:44:02.370
<i>All right.</i>

456
00:44:04.300 --> 00:44:09.070
<i>No. it's time to put an end to this.</i>

457
00:44:04.300 --> 00:44:09.070
<i>It's exhausting for everyone.</i>

458
00:44:11.480 --> 00:44:14.970
<i>I agree.</i>

459
00:44:11.480 --> 00:44:14.970
<i>You're absolutely right.</i>

460
00:44:15.880 --> 00:44:16.820
<i>Yes.</i>

461
00:44:41.740 --> 00:44:43.610
Your brother is dead.

462
00:44:45.410 --> 00:44:48.680
A creature like the one

463
00:44:45.410 --> 00:44:48.680
in the garden tore him apart.

464
00:44:49.920 --> 00:44:51.110
On the one hand.

465
00:44:51.350 --> 00:44:55.720
he made a huge mistake.

466
00:44:51.350 --> 00:44:55.720
venturing out ill-prepared.

467
00:44:57.720 --> 00:45:01.890
On the other hand. he was

468
00:44:57.720 --> 00:45:01.890
my son and I feel sorry for him.

469
00:45:03.460 --> 00:45:05.930
The animal that threatens us is a "cat":

470
00:45:06.130 --> 00:45:08.100
the most dangerous animal there is.

471
00:45:08.770 --> 00:45:12.570
It eats meat.

472
00:45:08.770 --> 00:45:12.570
children's flesh in particular.

473
00:45:13.040 --> 00:45:15.740
After lacerating its victim

474
00:45:13.040 --> 00:45:15.740
with its claws.

475
00:45:15.940 --> 00:45:17.810
it devours them with sharp teeth.

476
00:45:18.040 --> 00:45:20.140
The face and whole body of the victim.

477
00:45:20.950 --> 00:45:24.580
If you stay inside.

478
00:45:20.950 --> 00:45:24.580
you are protected.

479
00:45:25.550 --> 00:45:27.880
We have to be ready

480
00:45:28.090 --> 00:45:32.120
in case it invades the house

481
00:45:28.090 --> 00:45:32.120
or the garden.

482
00:46:24.840 --> 00:46:26.540
Our dear brother...

483
00:46:28.710 --> 00:46:33.180
we are all very sorry that

484
00:46:28.710 --> 00:46:33.180
you failed to exterminate the cat...

485
00:46:34.020 --> 00:46:35.610
<i>like I did.</i>

486
00:46:36.890 --> 00:46:38.790
<i>We are going to miss you...</i>

487
00:46:40.360 --> 00:46:42.620
<i>even though you made</i>

488
00:46:40.360 --> 00:46:42.620
<i>many mistakes.</i>

489
00:46:50.500 --> 00:46:52.170
<i>It's a real pity</i>

490
00:46:53.010 --> 00:46:55.500
<i>that it happened to you</i>

491
00:46:55.710 --> 00:47:00.670
<i>and that I couldn't use</i>

492
00:46:55.710 --> 00:47:00.670
<i>my knowledge to save you.</i>

493
00:47:08.220 --> 00:47:12.520
<i>My brother. I never expected...</i>

494
00:47:13.660 --> 00:47:17.220
<i>that things would turn out this way.</i>

495
00:47:18.760 --> 00:47:24.260
<i>I hoped you'd manage to survive</i>

496
00:47:18.760 --> 00:47:24.260
<i>with the supplies I procured.</i>

497
00:47:25.670 --> 00:47:28.040
<i>But the dangers are many.</i>

498
00:47:29.180 --> 00:47:30.940
<i>I am very sad.</i>

499
00:47:34.580 --> 00:47:37.850
Push three times on the chest.

500
00:47:34.580 --> 00:47:37.850
Forcefully.

501
00:47:38.420 --> 00:47:39.440
One.

502
00:47:39.920 --> 00:47:40.940
two.

503
00:47:41.220 --> 00:47:42.240
three.

504
00:47:43.090 --> 00:47:45.290
Afterwards you close her nose.

505
00:47:45.520 --> 00:47:48.430
open her mouth and blow.

506
00:48:59.500 --> 00:49:01.020
I'm pregnant.

507
00:49:01.930 --> 00:49:05.960
One boy. one girl. Twins.

508
00:49:06.340 --> 00:49:07.810
Two boys?

509
00:49:09.110 --> 00:49:10.870
No. a boy and a girl.

510
00:49:11.110 --> 00:49:12.700
Are you sure?

511
00:49:12.950 --> 00:49:13.970
Yes.

512
00:49:14.180 --> 00:49:15.550
Triplets?

513
00:49:17.480 --> 00:49:19.380
That's a bit much.

514
00:49:21.190 --> 00:49:23.160
You're right. twins.

515
00:49:26.730 --> 00:49:28.660
Turn round. do the same thing.

516
00:49:42.040 --> 00:49:44.070
Turn round. do the same thing.

517
00:49:53.990 --> 00:49:55.420
Okay.

518
00:50:00.390 --> 00:50:01.550
Dive in.

519
00:50:08.900 --> 00:50:09.930
Ready.

520
00:50:10.840 --> 00:50:13.670
One. two. three. go.

521
00:50:30.020 --> 00:50:30.960
<i>In a few months.</i>

522
00:50:31.190 --> 00:50:34.390
<i>your mother will give birth</i>

523
00:50:31.190 --> 00:50:34.390
<i>to two children and a dog.</i>

524
00:50:37.200 --> 00:50:39.860
<i>Some of you might not like this</i>

525
00:50:40.070 --> 00:50:43.040
<i>because they'll be sharing</i>

526
00:50:40.070 --> 00:50:43.040
<i>their room.</i>

527
00:50:43.240 --> 00:50:45.530
<i>their clothes. or even their toys.</i>

528
00:50:46.270 --> 00:50:47.240
<i>However.</i>

529
00:50:47.440 --> 00:50:49.270
<i>look on the bright side:</i>

530
00:50:49.480 --> 00:50:51.640
<i>you'll have two more people</i>

531
00:50:49.480 --> 00:50:51.640
<i>to support you.</i>

532
00:50:51.880 --> 00:50:53.440
<i>the family will be bigger.</i>

533
00:50:53.650 --> 00:50:57.310
<i>Let's all applaud your mother</i>

534
00:50:53.650 --> 00:50:57.310
<i>in anticipation of this gift.</i>

535
00:51:08.090 --> 00:51:10.060
I don't want to share my room.

536
00:51:10.260 --> 00:51:13.460
If you behave. you won't

537
00:51:10.260 --> 00:51:13.460
have to share with anyone.

538
00:51:13.670 --> 00:51:14.900
I will.

539
00:51:15.300 --> 00:51:17.960
I don't want to share

540
00:51:15.300 --> 00:51:17.960
my room either.

541
00:51:19.140 --> 00:51:23.170
<i>If I see improvements in</i>

542
00:51:19.140 --> 00:51:23.170
<i>your behavior and performance...</i>

543
00:51:23.410 --> 00:51:25.780
<i>I might avoid giving birth.</i>

544
00:51:26.580 --> 00:51:30.240
<i>But if things remain the same.</i>

545
00:51:26.580 --> 00:51:30.240
<i>you give me no choice.</i>

546
00:51:31.080 --> 00:51:34.020
<i>As for the dog.</i>

547
00:51:31.080 --> 00:51:34.020
<i>I don't want to hear a thing.</i>

548
00:51:34.250 --> 00:51:37.280
<i>I'll give birth as soon as possible.</i>

549
00:51:46.300 --> 00:51:49.200
Well done. honey.

550
00:51:46.300 --> 00:51:49.200
I mean well done. everyone.

551
00:51:49.440 --> 00:51:51.800
Dry yourself.

552
00:51:49.440 --> 00:51:51.800
Come and pick a prize.

553
00:51:53.440 --> 00:51:57.340
Don't touch it with wet hands

554
00:51:53.440 --> 00:51:57.340
or it won't stick afterwards.

555
00:51:58.810 --> 00:52:00.140
One more thing.

556
00:52:00.480 --> 00:52:03.380
Your performance was worse

557
00:52:00.480 --> 00:52:03.380
than last time.

558
00:52:03.620 --> 00:52:05.020
I need say no more.

559
00:52:07.790 --> 00:52:09.780
Oh. there's an airplane.

560
00:52:13.630 --> 00:52:15.290
It fell in the garden.

561
00:52:56.100 --> 00:52:58.370
No. not that much. It hurts.

562
00:53:00.740 --> 00:53:01.930
This much?

563
00:53:02.210 --> 00:53:03.270
Less.

564
00:53:07.710 --> 00:53:09.270
This much?

565
00:53:11.180 --> 00:53:12.380
That's it.

566
00:53:20.130 --> 00:53:24.620
Do you want me to lick you.

567
00:53:20.130 --> 00:53:24.620
then you'll give me a present?

568
00:53:24.860 --> 00:53:26.590
I have nothing to give you.

569
